This paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks trained for image object categorization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new unsupervised learning objective to improve the robustness of the learned representations, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the theoretical evidence and empirical evidence related to the optimization process, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a data augmentation technique to improve the invariance of the models, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
